					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 14th to 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment.</support>
								<extent>245 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>290</height>
										<width>200</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>165</height>
										<width>130</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>245 folios (+ 4 unfoliated modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and 3 at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>25 quires of mostly 10 leaves each, marked with catchwords and signatures in Hebrew letters at the end.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Slightly stained.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="2 " ruledLines="24" writtenLines="24">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Visible pricking and hard-point ruling.</p>
									<p>Hair side and flesh side distinguishable.</p>
									<p>Titles and inital words in larger characters. </p>
									<p>Hebrew signatures at the right-hand top corner of each fresh quire preserved in the earlier portion of the manuscript . </p>
									<p>Marginal notes and additions in various hands.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Italian semi-cursive script, unpunctuated, of the 14th to 15th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>English and Latin description of the manuscript pasted on the front flyleaves, fs003v and fs004v respectively.</p>
							<p>Folio 245v: astrological table with the names of the heavenly bodies influencing every hour of the night and day.</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p> Post-1600. Red leather, gold tooled. </p>
								<p>Spine: 'Anthologium Samuelis ben Juda. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Harley 5507.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
					</physDesc>
